  "text": "Lacps1 was characterized by mass spectrometry (MS) after trypsinolysis. Three tryptic peptides were detected, and their respective precursor ion masses and amino acid sequences were: m/z 1,242.682 (SPGTTAADLAVIK), m/z 1718.75 (SAGSSEYNYDNPIFR) and m/z 1992.69 (ANPSFGNTGFAGGINSAILR). The results of the mass spectrometry analysis and database search demonstrated that the identified peptides shared 100% sequence identity to peptides of two laccases from Pycnoporus coccineus M85-2 (UNIPROT: Q96TR6 and Q96VA5) [CITATION_1] . The amino acid sequences of the tryptic peptides covered about 9.3% of the amino acid sequences of both P. coccineus laccases.",
